<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-08-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="220" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/768½</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The French Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_JJJ2" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jusserand</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-18">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 18, 1917</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 19.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: As I told you when
                                I saw you this morning my Government would like to know whether, in
                                the opinion of the President, the Pope’s note, drawn up, as it seems
                                to have been, under inimical influences, demands an answer.</p>
                            <p>If the President thought it better to send one, my Government
                                consider it would be appropriate to concert as to what should be
                                said, so that a similar attitude be observed by those who fight on
                                the same side of the trench.</p>
                            <p>I should be much obliged if you would enable me to inform my
                                Government of the President’s views in the matter.</p>
                            <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_JJJ2">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jusserand</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>